Name: George St, West Perth
Main Risk: Poor road markings or no edge-lines
Description: I frequently see cars reversing up the freeway on-ramp as they have inadvertently chosen the incorrect lane due to poor road markings and signage. Reversing up the on-ramp is an obvious risk to other vehicles.  This particular lane lacks road markings indicating it is for Freeway South only. Motorists select this lane thinking it is a right turn lane for Murray street. When realising their error then reverse up the on/off-ramp in order to get into the correct lane.  An accident waiting to happen

Comment 1: Al: Cars mowing down cyclists. This has happened twice at this intersection in the last couple of weeks. The intersection has three different pedestrian/cyclist crossing lights and they are not timed well. Two of the three can be green but the first crossing is red. Cyclists flying down the hill may not notice the first section is red and attempt to cross but get mowed down by a car that has the right of way with a green light. Luckily the cyclists have survived these two incidents but watch out!
Comment 4: Mark: Cyclists cross this section every morning and afternoon as its a key access point to city and they constantly cross against the red light. A number have been hit by cars travelling along Wellington Street, two of which I have witnessed.

Name: 2, West Perth
Description: It is difficult to get on the Fwy south safely from the Murray/Elder St on ramp, at any time of the day, but especially in peak traffic, as the on ramp lane doesn't merge into the Fwy lane that continues south, but cars have to change lanes to get into the correct lane, while at the same time cars exiting the Fwy towards Mounts Bay Rd are changing into the entry lane, with only 300m space to do so. Entering here requires quick reflexes and good neck movement. I would call this road dangerous.
